headline: Tesla Rolls Out New Version of Its Self-Driving Software
summary: Ashok Elluswamy, Tesla’s vice president of AI software, tweeted Saturday night that version 13 of Tesla’s highest-level driver assistance software called Full Self-Driving began rolling out to customers.  Tesla believes it’s the product that will ultimately turn the millions of Tesla vehicles on roads into truly self-driving cars.  Coming into Monday trading, Tesla stock was up about 39% this year while the  was up about 26%.

headline: Trump’s Commerce Pick Hawked Buzzy Investments That Went Bust
summary: Cantor Fitzgerald CEO  Howard Lutnick  was pitching a startup that said it made a key component of self-driving cars, which would soon be valued at $2 billion.  “I’m brilliantly successful because I select brilliantly,” Lutnick said during a 2021 video call selling investors on  AEye  which had almost no revenue at the time.  Lutnick was behind a blank-check company, or SPAC, that planned to merge with AEye to take it public.

Tesla's stock performance can be partly attributed to the success of its disruptive and innovative culture.
